### Final Note on Tone

The mythology should feel ancient, inevitable, and true. Not fantasy — scripture. The reader should feel they are being told something that matters, something that explains why things are the way they are and what must be done about it.

The ending is positive despite destruction. The tragedy of FourTongue is real but resolved through grace. The urgency is existential but the promise is transcendence.

**"The sun will die. And only humanity can save it."**
